# Coding Standards

## Exports
- Named exports only. No default exports.

```typescript
// Bad
export default class Foo {}

// Good
export class Foo {}
export const createFoo = () => {};
```

## Types
- No `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow, or define a proper interface/type.

## File Scope
- One concern per file. Don't mix route handlers with business logic.

## Functions
- Keep functions small and pure where possible.
- Extract reusable logic into utility functions.

## Error Handling
- Use throw-and-catch. Let Express error middleware handle unexpected errors.

```typescript
// Good
if (!user) {
  throw new NotFoundError("User not found");
}
```

## Config
- All environment variables accessed through `src/config.ts`.
- No direct `process.env` reads outside the config module.

## Project Structure
- Backend code lives in `src/`.
- Frontend code lives in `src/ui/`.
- Do not restructure existing folders.
